trailingComments.value:
*
 * @desc An in8n-based localization service that we can configure on a {@link Viewer}.
 *
 * An I18nLocaleService can optionally be supplied to the {@link Viewer} constructor, to configure a central
 * service through which the Viewer and its {@link Plugin}s can obtain locale string translations. The I18nLocaleService
 * will then be available at {@link Viewer#localeService}.
 *
 * ## Usage
 *
 * Now we'll create a Viewer that's configured with an I18nLocaleService that will load translations from our files. We'll
 * use a {@link XKTLoaderPlugin} to load a BIM model, and we'll add a {@link NavCubePlugin}, which will show a NavCube in the
 * corner of the canvas.
 *
 * The NavCube faces will source their text from our translation files, according to the current locale.
 *
 * ````javascript
 * import {Viewer, I18nLocaleService, NavCubePlugin, XKTLoaderPlugin} from "xeokit-sdk.es.js";
 *
 * const viewer = new Viewer({
 *
 *      canvasId: "myCanvas",
 *
 *      localeService: new I18nLocaleService({
 *          messages: {
 *              "en": { // English
 *                  "NavCube.frontLabel": "Front",
 *                  "NavCube.backLabel": "Back",
 *                  "NavCube.topLabel": "Top",
 *                  "NavCube.bottomLabel": "Bottom",
 *                  "NavCube.leftLabel": "Left",
 *                  "NavCube.rightLabel": "Right"
 *              },
 *              "mi": { // Te Reo Māori
 *                "NavCube.frontLabel": "Mua",
 *                  "NavCube.backLabel": "Tuarā",
 *                  "NavCube.topLabel": "Runga",
 *                  "NavCube.bottomLabel": "Raro",
 *                  "NavCube.leftLabel": "Mauī",
 *                "NavCube.rightLabel": "Tika"
 *              },
 *              "fr": { // Francais
 *                  "NavCube.frontLabel": "Avant",
 *                  "NavCube.backLabel": "Arrière",
 *                  "NavCube.topLabel": "Supérieur",
 *                  "NavCube.bottomLabel": "Inférieur",
 *                  "NavCube.leftLabel": "Gauche",
 *                  "NavCube.rightLabel": "Droit"
 *              }
 *          },
 *          locale: "en"
 *      })
 *  });
 *
 * viewer.camera.eye = [-3.93, 2.85, 27.01];
 * viewer.camera.look = [4.40, 3.72, 8.89];
 * viewer.camera.up = [-0.01, 0.99, 0.03];
 *
 * const navCubePlugin = new NavCubePlugin(viewer, {
 *      canvasID: "myNavCubeCanvas"
 *  });
 *
 * const xktLoader = new XKTLoaderPlugin(viewer);
 *
 * const model = xktLoader.load({
 *     id: "myModel",
 *     src: "./models/xkt/Duplex.ifc.xkt",
 *     edges: true
 * });
 * ````
 *
 * We can dynamically switch our Viewer to a different locale at any time, which will update the text on the
 * faces of our NavCube:
 *
 * ````javascript
 * viewer.localeService.locale = "fr"; // Switch to French
 * ````
 *
 * We can also get an event whenever we switch locales, which is useful for triggering UI elements to
 * refresh themselves with translations for the new locale. Internally, the NavCube subscribes to this
 * event, fetching new strings for itself via {@link I18nLocaleService#translate} each time the event is fired.
 *
 * ````javascript
 * viewer.localeService.on("updated", () => {
 *     console.log( viewer.localeService.translate("NavCube.leftLabel") );
 *     // "Gauche"
 * });
 * ````
 *
 * @extends {LocaleService}
 * @since 2.0

trailingComments.value:
*
     * Sets the current locale and returns a Promise.
     *
     * The given locale must be in the list of available locales returned by {@link I18nLocaleService#locales}.
     *
     * When the local has been set and translations are loaded, the I18nLocaleService will fire a "updated" event
     * and resolve the Promise.
     *
     * At that point, it's possible to get the translations for the locale via {@link I18nLocaleService#translate}
     * and {@link I18nLocaleService#translatePlurals}.
     *
     * The Promise is rejected if the locale is unrecognized, or the translation files could not be loaded.
     *
     * @param {String} locale The locale to set.
     * @return {Promise}
